job_history.work_description: Develop or coordinate fitness and wellness programs or services. Supervise fitness or wellness workers, such as fitness instructors, recreation workers, nutritionists, and health educators. Conduct or facilitate training sessions or seminars for wellness and fitness staff. Develop fitness or wellness classes, such as yoga, aerobics, weightlifting, and aquatics, ensuring a diversity of class offerings.

Manage or oversee fitness or recreation facilities, ensuring safe and clean facilities and equipment. Operate, and instruct others in, proper operation of fitness equipment, such as weight machines, exercise bicycles, benches, hand weights, and fitness assessment devices.

Greet new arrivals to activities, introducing them to other participants, explaining facility rules, and encouraging participation. Officiate at sporting events, games, or competitions, to maintain standards of play and to ensure that game rules are observed.
Confer with customers by telephone or in person to provide information about products or services, take or enter orders, cancel accounts, or obtain details of complaints.

skills.name: Fitness Program Development
skills.explanation: Developed or coordinated fitness and wellness programs or services, showing a solid working proficiency.

skills.name: Leadership
skills.explanation: Supervised fitness or wellness workers and conducted training sessions, indicating some practical experience in leadership.

skills.name: Fitness Instruction
skills.explanation: Instructed others in proper operation of fitness equipment and developed fitness or wellness classes, suggesting strong proficiency.

skills.name: Facility Management
skills.explanation: Managed or oversaw fitness or recreation facilities, ensuring safe and clean facilities and equipment, showing a solid working proficiency.

skills.name: Customer Service
skills.explanation: Conferred with customers by telephone or in person to provide information about products or services, indicating some practical experience in customer service.

skills.name: Event Officiation
skills.explanation: Officiated at sporting events, games, or competitions, maintaining standards of play and ensuring game rules were observed, indicating some practical experience.

skills.name: Personal Training
skills.explanation: Obtained a Certified Personal Training Certification, suggesting a solid working proficiency in personal training.
